---
title: fix for gbm.plot
layout: post
---



I'm currently in the process of writing a report using boosted regression trees.  I'm currently using guidelines provided by Elith et al - <a href="http://avesbiodiv.mncn.csic.es/estadistica/bt1.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>, and <a href="http://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/dismo/vignettes/brt.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>. They provide the function gbm.step, which performs 10-fold cross validation on the boosted regression tree.</p>
<p style="color: #222222; text-align: left;">It also has a nifty gbm.plot function.</p>
<p style="color: #222222; text-align: left;">Which kept giving me this error:</p>

<blockquote style="font-style: italic !important; color: #222222;"><span style="color: #ff0000;">Error: could not find function "windows" </span></blockquote>
<p style="color: #222222; text-align: left;">The reason is that I am using a mac...which uses X11() instead of windows() - I found this out thanks to this website here: http://doingbayesiandataanalysis.blogspot.com.au/2011/09/for-linux-macos-users-easy-fix-for.html</p>
<p style="color: #222222; text-align: left;">So I simply found the source code for gbm.plot, and replaced windows(...) with X11(...)</p>
<p style="color: #222222; text-align: left;">Hopefully this will prove helpful to someone.</p>